<p class="eyebrow"><a href="/docs/">Documentation</a> / VoiceML SDKs</p>
<h1>Official client libraries for the VoiceML REST API.</h1>
<p class="lede">Eight language SDKs for VoiceTel's outbound voice and answering-machine-detection service. All hand-written, all open-source under MIT, all targeting {{ voicemlSdks.targetApi }}. Each SDK covers the same {{ voicemlSdks.operationCount }} operations across {{ voicemlSdks.resourceGroupCount }} resource groups: {{ voicemlSdks.resourceGroups }}.</p>

<p class="hero-actions">
	<a class="btn btn-primary" href="{{ voicemlSdks.source }}">Browse GitHub</a>
	<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="{{ apiSpecs.voiceml.urlPath }}">API reference</a>
</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>SDKs</h2>
	<div class="oss-cards">
		{% for sdk in voicemlSdks.sdks %}
		<article class="oss-card">
			<header class="oss-card__header">
				<span class="oss-card__icon">{% icon "github" %}</span>
				<h3 class="oss-card__title"><a href="{{ sdk.repo }}">{{ sdk.name }}</a></h3>
			</header>
			<p class="oss-card__description">{{ sdk.description }}</p>
			<p class="oss-card__install">
				{% if sdk.installLabel %}<span class="oss-card__install-label">{{ sdk.installLabel }}</span>{% endif %}<code>{{ sdk.install }}</code>
			</p>
			<p class="oss-card__url"><a href="{{ sdk.repo }}">{{ sdk.repo | replace("https://", "") }}</a></p>
		</article>
		{% endfor %}
	</div>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>What every SDK gets you</h2>
	<ul class="features-grid">
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "code-slash" %}</span>
			<h3>Strongly typed end-to-end</h3>
			<p>Every request body and response payload is a typed struct, class, or record in the host language. No untyped <code>Hash</code> or <code>map[string]any</code> in your call sites.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "shield-check" %}</span>
			<h3>Twilio-shape wire format</h3>
			<p>Same paths under <code>2010-04-01/Accounts/{AccountSid}/…</code>, same HTTP Basic auth, same <code>{code, message, more_info, status}</code> error envelope. Existing Twilio client constructors translate one-to-one.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "activity" %}</span>
			<h3>Structured errors</h3>
			<p>Status-keyed exception types — <code>AuthenticationError</code>, <code>NotFoundError</code>, <code>ConflictError</code>, <code>RateLimitError</code>, <code>ServerError</code>. Catch broadly or pattern-match by class.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<span class="feature-icon" aria-hidden="true">{% icon "list-check" %}</span>
			<h3>Retries and pagination built in</h3>
			<p>Auto-retry on 429 / 5xx with <code>Retry-After</code> honored and exponential backoff capped at 8s. Cursor pagination via <code>next_page_uri</code>; Python and TypeScript ship an <code>iterate()</code> helper for the <code>/Calls</code> list.</p>
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="voiceml-sdk-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="voiceml-sdk-cta-heading">Migrating from Twilio?</h2>
	<p>The constructor signature is the same <code>(account_sid, secret)</code> shape. Swap the import and point at <code>voiceml.voicetel.com</code> — your existing voice markup keeps working without changes.</p>
	<p class="hero-actions">
		<a class="btn btn-primary" href="/voiceml/migrate/">Migration guide</a>
		<a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/voiceml/validator/">Validate markup</a>
	</p>
</aside>
